is empty, is it?

234
00:13:14,875 --> 00:13:16,625
This sure takes me back.

235
00:13:16,708 --> 00:13:18,291
I wonder if doodles
are still on my desk.

236
00:13:18,375 --> 00:13:21,083
Doubtful, the school changes
out the desks every year.

237
00:13:21,166 --> 00:13:22,958
Let's check out
the cafeteria after this.

238
00:13:23,041 --> 00:13:24,583
I wanna see the old gym.

239
00:13:24,666 --> 00:13:25,791
Good idea, Kaoru!

240
00:13:25,875 --> 00:13:27,375
Hey! If you're gonna
barge in here like that

241
00:13:27,458 --> 00:13:30,041
then why'd we have to sneak in
here in these stupid disguises?

242
00:13:30,125 --> 00:13:31,041
Don't worry about it.

243
00:13:31,125 --> 00:13:32,541
There's no one here
to catch us.

244
00:13:37,500 --> 00:13:39,083
If the teacher finds us-

245
00:13:39,166 --> 00:13:41,875
-we'll have a hard time
explaining why we snuck in.

246
00:13:41,958 --> 00:13:44,208
Shut up you guys!

247
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:47,291
Keep your lips
zipped, got it?

248
00:13:49,375 --> 00:13:51,458
Haruhi's the cutest
thing I've ever seen!

249
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:57,291
It's alright, he's gone.
But you guys, we came here

250
00:13:57,375 --> 00:13:59,208
to get the scoop on Shiro,
so what do you think

251
00:13:59,291 --> 00:14:01,375
we should do now?

252
00:14:01,458 --> 00:14:02,833
Well, Here's
something interesting.

253
00:14:04,666 --> 00:14:06,083
What'd you find?

254
00:14:09,458 --> 00:14:11,625
Hey! That's Shiro!

255
00:14:11,708 --> 00:14:13,416
So he's in the
Classical Music Club.

256
00:14:15,125 --> 00:14:16,375
He looks like
he's enjoying himself.

257
00:14:16,458 --> 00:14:19,041
It's nice to see him with
a smile on his face.

258
00:14:19,125 --> 00:14:22,250
I had no idea he
could look so sweet.

259
00:14:24,833 --> 00:14:25,958
Yeah.

260
00:14:29,250 --> 00:14:31,250
There he is!
There's Shiro-chan!

261
00:14:35,333 --> 00:14:37,958
Excuse me, Takaoji?

262
00:14:38,041 --> 00:14:39,500
I'm sorry, but have you been
practicing the new piece

263
00:14:39,583 --> 00:14:41,666
teacher gave us?

264
00:14:41,750 --> 00:14:43,791
The new piece? Not really.

265
00:14:43,875 --> 00:14:45,041
If you want I can show it
to you. Do you wanna

266
00:14:45,125 --> 00:14:47,416
come play it with me?

267
00:14:47,500 --> 00:14:49,750
No thanks, you go ahead.

268
00:14:49,833 --> 00:14:51,666
After all, there's
only one grand piano.

269
00:14:51,750 --> 00:14:53,541
You should use it, Kahmishiro.

270
00:14:54,250 --> 00:14:57,541
Thank you! I will then!

271
00:14:57,625 --> 00:15:00,250
And if you want to join me
just let me know.

272
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:36,083
Pardon me, mademoiselle.

273
00:15:37,083 --> 00:15:40,791
I've never seen a rose more
lovely than you, my dear.

274
00:15:40,875 --> 00:15:43,041
Here, this is for you.

275
00:15:43,833 --> 00:15:45,708
I was wondering if you could
tell me anything about

276
00:15:45,791 --> 00:15:49,416
that young lady playing
the piano. Do you know her?

277
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:51,541
That's Hina Kameeshido.

278
00:15:51,625 --> 00:15:53,000
Her name is Hina?

279
00:15:53,083 --> 00:15:55,833
That's right, But you better
not fall in love with her.

280
00:15:55,916 --> 00:15:57,083
Why?

281
00:15:57,166 --> 00:16:00,291
Didn't you know? Hina
has to move away soon.

282
00:16:00,375 --> 00:16:03,291
Her dad just got a new job
in Germany, so they have to

283
00:16:03,375 --> 00:16:05,291
move there at
the end of the week.

284
00:16:05,375 --> 00:16:06,916
What do you
think you're doing?!

285
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:09,250
I want you idiots
to leave immediately!

286
00:16:11,750 --> 00:16:14,166
Put me down!
What are you doing?!

287
00:16:18,208 --> 00:16:20,666
Let me go! Just put me down!
Where do you think...

288
00:16:20,750 --> 00:16:23,750
It's time to go, guys.
Quit thrashing around.

289
00:16:27,333 --> 00:16:29,291
What is your problem,
you big idiot?!

290
00:16:29,375 --> 00:16:31,666
I'm sorry but
you're the idiot.

291
00:16:31,750 --> 00:16:33,416
You said that you wanted
me to teach you how

292
00:16:33,500 --> 00:16:35,875
to make women happy.
But that's not it, is it?

293
00:16:35,958 --> 00:16:39,416
You're not concerned with the
happinesss of just any woman.

294
00:16:39,500 --> 00:16:42,875
You've got your sights set on
one woman in particular.

295
00:16:43,666 --> 00:16:47,458
You only care about one,
and that's Hina Kamishiro.

296
00:16:50,500 --> 00:16:52,791
But I'm afraid there's
nothing I can do

297
00:16:52,875 --> 00:16:54,875
to help you with that, Shiro.

298
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:58,458
Listen, Shiro.
I know that I told you,

299
00:16:58,541 --> 00:17:00,833
it's the job of a host
to make women happy.

300
00:17:00,916 --> 00:17:02,750
But when you care
for someone, you must

301
00:17:02,833 --> 00:17:05,541
find the courage to express
what is in your heart.

302
00:17:05,625 --> 00:17:09,208
You have to tell her
how you feel about her.

303
00:17:09,291 --> 00:17:12,708
You didn't come to me looking
to become a full-fledged host.

304
00:17:14,166 --> 00:17:16,708
You want to be
a full-fledged man.

305
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:21,625
It doesn't matter anymore.
I've run out of time.

306
00:17:21,708 --> 00:17:27,333
I just I wanted to hear her
play before she left for good.

307
00:17:27,416 --> 00:17:28,708
That's all.

308
00:17:29,583 --> 00:17:30,916
That piece she played.

309
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:34,541
It's Mozart's Sonata in D major
for 2 Pianos, isn't it?

310
00:17:51,458 --> 00:17:54,375
Wait a minute, since when
is there a grand piano

311
00:17:54,458 --> 00:17:55,458
in this room?

312
00:17:55,541 --> 00:17:57,541
Well, this is a music
room, after all.

313
00:17:57,625 --> 00:17:59,500
So why wouldn't it
have a grand piano?

314
00:17:59,583 --> 00:18:01,458
It is a music room, after all.

315
00:18:01,541 --> 00:18:02,875
It is a music room.

316
00:18:02,958 --> 00:18:05,875
It's always been there.
We just had it covered up.

317
00:18:30,125 --> 00:18:31,625
Awesome.

318
00:18:35,125 --> 00:18:37,166
Hey Takaoji. I noticed
that you're always

319
00:18:37,250 --> 00:18:41,166
listening to me when I'm
playing. Do you like the piano?

320
00:18:41,250 --> 00:18:44,166
If so then why don't
we learn to play together?

321
00:18:46,916 --> 00:18:52,333
She played beautifully, but it
wasn't the piano that I liked.

322
00:18:52,416 --> 00:18:54,541
For the next week you
will spend your mornings,

323
00:18:54,625 --> 00:18:57,833
lunches, recesses,
and free-time after school

324
00:18:57,916 --> 00:19:00,041
in piano lessons with me.

325
00:19:00,125 --> 00:19:02,500
But, why?

326
00:19:02,583 --> 00:19:05,125
You wanted to be
my apprentice, right?

327
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:08,708
Besides, that young lady
looked like she wanted

328
00:19:08,791 --> 00:19:12,125
nothing more than
to play piano with you.

329
00:19:52,541 --> 00:19:55,708
Welcome, princess,
we've been waiting.

330
00:19:55,791 --> 00:20:03,125
I present to you, Shiro
Takaoji's piano recital.

331
00:20:13,291 --> 00:20:16,166
If you please, princess.

332
00:20:19,958 --> 00:20:22,083
Let's play together, Hina.

333
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:24,833
Okay!

334
00:20:48,708 --> 00:20:51,250
We did a good thing.

335
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:55,416
He loves with all his heart.
So I guess that's

336
00:20:55,500 --> 00:20:58,833
one more way Shiro
takes after you, huh, senpai?

337
00:20:58,916 --> 00:21:01,791
Why, yes, I'd say so.

338
00:21:09,750 --> 00:21:12,666
So you've been exchanging
emails with Hina everyday

339
00:21:12,750 --> 00:21:13,916
now that she's in Germany?

340
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:15,750
Yeah, more or less.

341
00:21:15,833 --> 00:21:17,958
I like her but she can get
pretty jealous for

342
00:21:18,041 --> 00:21:19,916
an elementary school girl.

343
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:22,416
She'd be upset if she knew
I was with you ladies,

344
00:21:22,500 --> 00:21:24,166
so let's keep this
our little secret.

345
00:21:24,250 --> 00:21:25,750
Oh! Isn't he the cutest?!

346
00:21:25,833 --> 00:21:27,083
His little girlfriend
is so lucky!

347
00:21:27,166 --> 00:21:28,625
I wish I had a little
brother just like him!

348
00:21:28,708 --> 00:21:29,958
Naughty boys are the best!

349
00:21:30,041 --> 00:21:31,458
I could kiss you.

350
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:36,875
You brat, what are you doing.
Those are my guests.

351
00:21:36,958 --> 00:21:39,250
Well, it looks like they've
found someone they like better.

352
00:21:39,333 --> 00:21:41,791
It was so easy
to steal your customers.

353
00:21:41,875 --> 00:21:44,625
I think there's
a new host king in town.

354
00:21:45,958 --> 00:21:48,166
I thought he'd make it through
without exploding this time.

355
00:21:48,250 --> 00:21:51,041
We should've known he was
gonna blow up sooner or later.

356
00:21:51,125 --> 00:21:55,166
Shiro really does have a lot
in common with Tamaki-senpai.

357
00:21:55,250 --> 00:21:57,666
I get the feeling that senpai
was also a spoiled brat

358
00:21:57,750 --> 00:21:58,833
when he was a kid.

359
00:21:58,916 --> 00:22:00,250
I was not a spoiled brat!

360
00:22:00,333 --> 00:22:02,083
I was nothing like him
when I was a kid!

361
00:22:02,166 --> 00:22:04,541
I was a sweet, innocent,
precocious, adorable child!

362
00:22:04,625 --> 00:22:06,416
You hear me?!

363
00:23:12,333 --> 00:23:14,041
All right,
we're headed to the pool!

364
00:23:14,125 --> 00:23:16,291
We'll finally get to see
Haruhi in a swimsuit!

365
00:23:16,375 --> 00:23:19,416
Oh, no! Honey-senpai is being
pulled away by the current!

366
00:23:19,500 --> 00:23:22,000
Next time,
"Jungle Pool SOS"

367
00:23:22,083 --> 00:23:24,625
The Ouran Host Club
will be waiting for you!

368
00:23:24,708 --> 00:23:26,666
We'll see you then!

